definition:
Fibonacci polynomials are defined recursively as follow $$F_n(x):=
\left\{
 \begin{array}{ll}
  1 & {\rm if~} n=1;\\
  x & {\rm if~} n=2;\\
  x F_{n-1}(x)+F_{n-2}(x), & {\rm if~} n>2.
 \end{array}
\right.$$ The main (and obvious) property of this polynomials is that
$F_n(1)$ is $n^{\rm th}$ number in Fibonacci sequence.
